# Line-ending policy for sdk-kmp.
#
# NOTE: .gitattributes do not cross repository boundaries, so this submodule does
# not inherit the workspace-root .gitattributes. It needs its own.
#
# Git for Windows ships core.autocrlf=true as a SYSTEM default
# (C:/Program Files/Git/etc/gitconfig), which checks text files out as CRLF on a
# fresh Windows clone.
#
# `gradlew` is a POSIX shell script executed on Linux and macOS — this repo is built
# on the Linux VM (linuxX64), on a Mac (the XCFramework for sdk-ios), and on Windows.
# A CRLF checkout gives it a `#!/bin/sh\r` shebang, which fails with an obscure
# "no such file or directory". `gradlew.bat` is the opposite: a Windows batch file,
# conventionally CRLF and safest pinned that way. `gradle-wrapper.jar` must never be
# touched by any text filter.
#
# Local `core.autocrlf` config is machine-local and never travels with the repo — a
# fresh clone elsewhere gets the system default. This attribute travels; the local
# override does not.
#
# Deliberately targeted rather than a blanket `* text=auto eol=lf`, which would
# rewrite the whole working tree on next checkout for no benefit.
gradlew                text eol=lf
gradlew.bat            text eol=crlf
gradle-wrapper.jar     binary
*.sh                   text eol=lf
